## SECTION 4 — AUDIENCE INTELLIGENCE

**Who they are:**
Nail-engaged women, 22–38, who follow trends actively but book salon appointments rather than DIY. They consume Byrdie, Who What Wear, and nail TikTok. They are not nail technicians. They want to arrive at their appointment knowing what to ask for. They also use posts like this to plan ahead — to know what's coming before it arrives so they feel ahead of the curve rather than reactive.

**What they want from this post:**
A complete, confident overview of the full 2026 nail year — what's happening right now (summer), what's coming (fall/winter), and how the season shapes their choices. They want editorial perspective, not just a list. They want to understand the story behind the trends, not just the trend names.

**What frustrates them about current content:**
- Lists of 7–19 trends with no temporal context — they don't know which are for now vs later
- Generic "what's trending" content that doesn't commit to a point of view
- Posts written as if every trend applies equally — no acknowledgement that some trends are subtle, some require a salon, some are DIY-accessible
